    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\n[`termfeatures.osc52`](https://neovim.io/doc/user/provider/#clipboard-osc52) will never be automatically set to neither `true` or `false` whenever using the version before or after switched to detect via DA1 (Primary Device Attributes) #34860 when using Konsole.\nManually set it to `true` will work.\nhttps://terminalguide.namepad.de/seq/csi_sc/ states Konsole will always reply DA1 with `ESC[?1;2c`\nKonsole seems not supporting `XTGETTCAP` that used by neovim 0.11 #34472: https://bugs.kde.org/show_bug.cgi?id=507017\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```\nnvim --clean\n:lua=vim.g.clipboard\n:lua=vim.g.termfeatures\n:checkhealth vim.provider\n```\n\nKonsole:\n```\nnil\nnil\n[...]\nClipboard (optional)\n- ⚠ WARNING No clipboard tool found. Clipboard registers (\"+ and \"*) will not work.\n  - ADVICE:\n    - :help clipboard\n[...]\n```\n\ntmux in Konsole:\n```\nnil\nnil\n[...]\nClipboard (optional)\n- ✅ OK Clipboard tool found: tmux\n[...]\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nAuto detected.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.11.7 and 0.12.1\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nvim 9.2.106 doesn't support OSC 52\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nNixOS 25.11\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nKonsole 25.08.3\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\n`xterm-256color` and `tmux`\n\n### Installation\n\n`nixpkgs#neovim` on [`nixos-25.11`](https://github.com/NixOS/nixpkgs/blob/7e495b747b51f95ae15e74377c5ce1fe69c1765f/pkgs/by-name/ne/neovim-unwrapped/package.nix#L98) for `0.11.7` and [`nixos-unstable`](https://github.com/NixOS/nixpkgs/blob/4bd9165a9165d7b5e33ae57f3eecbcb28fb231c9/pkgs/by-name/ne/neovim-unwrapped/package.nix#L105) for `0.12.1`",
