            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "I'm having trouble understanding the problem statement here, but it sounds like you're saying Konsole always responds with `ESC[?1;2c` to the Device Attributes Request and that Konsole does not support XTGETTCAP.\n\nIf that is correct then this is not a Neovim bug: Neovim is doing everything it can to ask the terminal \"do you support OSC 52\" and the terminal is replying \"no I don't\". So this is a Konsole bug, not a Neovim bug.\n\nIn this case manually setting `g:termfeatures` is the correct (and only) thing you can do.",
