            "body": "`printf $'\\e[0c' | hexdump -C` gives me\n```\n00000000  1b 5b 30 63                                       |.[0c|\n00000004\n```\nso it's not `ESC[?1;2c` but the replied `ESC[0c` still not containing `52` that matched by the DA1 detecting: https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/bc6d946cca422c770e792a62d7454387d79065e2/runtime/plugin/osc52.lua#L41-L49\n\nI've filed this upstream: https://bugs.kde.org/show_bug.cgi?id=519031\n",
